chatgpt_program: SELECT Id, Maker FROM car_makers WHERE Id IN (SELECT Maker FROM model_list GROUP BY Maker HAVING COUNT() >= 2) AND Id IN (SELECT MakeId FROM car_names GROUP BY MakeId HAVING COUNT() > 3)

metadata.query: SELECT T1.Model FROM CAR_NAMES AS T1 JOIN CARS_DATA AS T2 ON T1.MakeId  =  T2.Id ORDER BY T2.horsepower ASC LIMIT 1;
metadata.question: What is the model of the car with the smallest amount of horsepower?

chatgpt_program: SELECT Model FROM cars_data WHERE Horsepower = (SELECT min(Horsepower) FROM cars_data)

metadata.query: SELECT t1.name FROM employee AS t1 JOIN evaluation AS t2 ON t1.Employee_ID  =  t2.Employee_ID ORDER BY t2.bonus DESC LIMIT 1
metadata.question: Which employee received the biggest bonus? Give me the employee name.

chatgpt_program: SELECT Name FROM employee JOIN evaluation ON employee.Employee_ID = evaluation.Employee_ID ORDER BY Bonus DESC LIMIT 1

chatgpt_program: SELECT DISTINCT Template_Type_Code FROM Templates

metadata.query: SELECT T1.first_name ,  T1.middle_name ,  T1.last_name ,  T1.student_id FROM Students AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.student_id GROUP BY T1.student_id HAVING count(*)  =  2
metadata.question: Who are enrolled in 2 degree programs in one semester? List the first name, middle name and last name and the id.

chatgpt_program:
SELECT S.first_name, S.middle_name, S.last_name, S.student_id
FROM Students AS S
JOIN Student_Enrolment AS SE ON S.student_id = SE.student_id
WHERE SE.degree_program_id IN (
SELECT degree_program_id
FROM Student_Enrolment
WHERE semester_id = 1
GROUP BY student_id
HAVING count(*) = 2
)

metadata.query: SELECT DISTINCT T2.semester_id FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id WHERE degree_summary_name  =  'Master' INTERSECT SELECT DISTINCT T2.semester_id FROM Degree_Programs AS T1 JOIN Student_Enrolment AS T2 ON T1.degree_program_id  =  T2.degree_program_id WHERE degree_summary_name  =  'Bachelor'
metadata.question: Find the semester when both Master students and Bachelor students got enrolled in.

chatgpt_program:
SELECT semester_name FROM Semesters WHERE semester_id IN
(SELECT SE1.semester_id FROM Student_Enrolment AS SE1 JOIN Degree_Programs AS DP1 ON SE1.degree_program_id = DP1.degree_program_id WHERE DP1.degree_summary_name = 'Master')
AND semester_id IN
(SELECT SE2.semester_id FROM Student_Enrolment AS SE2 JOIN Degree_Programs AS DP2 ON SE2.degree_program_id = DP2.degree_program_id WHERE DP2.degree_summary_name = 'Bachelor')

metadata.query: SELECT T3.name FROM Friend AS T1 JOIN Highschooler AS T2 ON T1.student_id  =  T2.id JOIN Highschooler AS T3 ON T1.friend_id  =  T3.id WHERE T2.name  =  "Kyle"
metadata.question: Return the names of friends of the high school student Kyle.

chatgpt_program:
SELECT Highschooler.name
FROM Highschooler
JOIN Friend ON Highschooler.ID = Friend.friend_id
WHERE Highschooler.name = 'Kyle'

chatgpt_program: SELECT created, state, phone_number FROM VOTES JOIN CONTESTANTS ON VOTES.contestant_number = CONTESTANTS.contestant_number WHERE CONTESTANTS.contestant_name = 'Tabatha Gehling'

metadata.query: select count(*) from countries as t1 join car_makers as t2 on t1.countryid  =  t2.country group by t1.countryid having count(*)  >  2
metadata.question: How many countries has more than 2 car makers ?

chatgpt_program:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT Country)FROM car_makers
WHERE Country IN (
SELECT Country
FROM car_makers
GROUP BY Country
HAVING COUNT(DISTINCT Maker) > 2
)

metadata.query: SELECT count(*) FROM FLIGHTS AS T1 JOIN AIRPORTS AS T2 ON T1.DestAirport  =  T2.AirportCode JOIN AIRLINES AS T3 ON T3.uid  =  T1.Airline WHERE T2.City  =  "Aberdeen" AND T3.Airline  =  "United Airlines"
metadata.question: How many United Airlines flights go to City 'Aberdeen'?

chatgpt_program: SELECT COUNT(*) FROM flights AS F JOIN airlines AS A ON F.Airline = A.Abbreviation JOIN airports AS S ON F.SourceAirport = S.AirportCode WHERE A.Airline = 'United Airlines' AND S.City = 'Aberdeen'

metadata.query: SELECT T3.Name ,  T2.Course FROM course_arrange AS T1 JOIN course AS T2 ON T1.Course_ID  =  T2.Course_ID JOIN teacher AS T3 ON T1.Teacher_ID  =  T3.Teacher_ID ORDER BY T3.Name
metadata.question: Show names of teachers and the courses they are arranged to teach in ascending alphabetical order of the teacher's name.

chatgpt_program: SELECT teacher.Name, course.Course FROM teacher JOIN course_arrange ON teacher.Teacher_ID = course_arrange.Teacher_ID JOIN course ON course_arrange.Course_ID = course.Course_ID ORDER BY teacher.Name ASC
